  "prompt": "From which institute should I learn post production and lightning, sound camera etc for my YouTube channel in Delhi?",
  "response": "If you're looking to learn post-production, lighting, sound, camera work, and other related skills for your YouTube channel in Delhi, there are several reputed institutes you can consider:\n\n1. **Film and Television Institute of India (FTII) Delhi:** FTII offers various short-term courses and workshops that could be beneficial.\n\n2. **Sri Aurobindo Centre for Arts and Communication (SACAC):** SACAC offers courses in creative filmmaking, photography, and multimedia, which encompass the skills you are looking to develop.\n\n3. **Indian Institute of Photography (IIP):** IIP offers photography courses along with training in post-production and lighting, which could be useful for your YouTube content creation.\n\n4. **AAFT School of Cinema:** AAFT offers courses in filmmaking, including post-production, sound, and camera techniques.\n\n5. **MAC (Media and Arts College):** MAC offers various multimedia and film courses which can provide you with the necessary skills for high-quality video production.\n\n6. **Delhi Film Institute:** They offer courses in film and television production, sound design, and editing.\n\nAdditionally, many institutions offer workshops and short courses that may fit your needs for specific skills like post-production or sound design. It's also valuable to check out community meetups, online forums, and local filmmaking groups where you can learn and network with other content creators. \n\nRemember to review the curriculum and faculty backgrounds of each institute to ensure they meet your specific needs for YouTube content creation.",
